[This is still disturbing news. Even though the cow evidently did not have
BSE, it was still an _unhealthy cow_ (by their own admittance), that made
it to the slaughter house, without the proper documentation. One animal
with obvious signs and defective papers gets through the system, one can
safely assume this is not a unique event. So, this only proves that the
potential for BSE infected cow to make it into the food chain. Fortunately
this time it was seen and it turned out to not be BSE. The others? Since
the entire herd was slaughtered, is there a funding buy-out since this has
turned out not to BSE?. With accidents like this, it is unlikely France
will meet its goal. - Mod.TG
